{"questionId":"10072","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Table 1</strong> provides information about Fairland.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Table 1</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/a6092d760b91ad7eab33bdf5973fe90c5835223d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><strong>Figure 6</strong> illustrates Fairland’s demand (<em>D</em>) for and supply (<em>S</em>) of low-wage labour.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Figure 6</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><img src=\"__IMG__/ae3401d5831a37bcadb0bc259fb02a584aa84061.png\"></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">In order to raise the living standards of low-wage workers, the government of Fairland has decided to impose a minimum wage of $10 per hour.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The marginal rates of income tax in Fairland are given in <strong>Table 2</strong>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>Table 2</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><img src=\"__IMG__/f4d7395216a921941a7c79890fe01c05d9e50c0f.png\"></strong></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Define the term <em>marginal rate of tax</em>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/d6736f14c4c233a8dd4f4ffb9d31f02a65af4c64.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"10072","referenceCode":"19M.3.HL.TZ0.3e.i","subjectId":"48-dp-economics","title":"Define the term marginal rate of tax.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["First exams 2022","Last exams 2021","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.4 Economics of inequality and poverty","3.4.8 The role of taxation in reducing poverty, income and wealth inequalities","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","3.4 Economics of inequality and poverty","First exams 2022","Unit 3: Macroeconomics","Last exams 2021","Section 2: Macroeconomics","2.3 Macroecon